#open-question(title: [Can the Garfinkel Tripartite Interoception Framework Be Validated in ME/CFS?])[
The single most tractable study suggested by the interoceptive model: a case-control design (ME/CFS n=120, healthy n=120, anxiety disorder n=60) completing the heartbeat detection task (HBDT) with confidence ratings (Garfinkel protocol @Garfinkel2015interoceptionAccuracy), Multidimensional Assessment of Interoceptive Awareness (MAIA-2), Toronto Alexithymia Scale (TAS-20), and plasma cytokines (IL-6, TNF-$alpha$, IL-1$beta$). Primary prediction: interoceptive accuracy (HBDT) < controls, interoceptive sensibility (MAIA) > controls, metacognitive awareness (confidence-accuracy gap) < controls — a dissociation pattern predicted by the corrupted-afferent model and not characteristic of anxiety disorders (high both) or healthy individuals (low sensibility, high accuracy). This mech=5, dx=4 study would provide the psychophysical validation the interoceptive model currently lacks and could identify the Interoceptive Accuracy-Sensibility Gap (IASG) as a candidate diagnostic index. Cytokine mediation analysis would test the inflammation→interoception pathway directly. (Origin: brainstorm) @QuadtCritchleyGarfinkel2018interoception @ValenzuelaMoguillansky2017bodyAwarenessFM @Maroti2017alexithymiaCFS
] <oq:tripartite-interoception-mecfs>
